LogGroupName.Description: Name of the Amazon CloudWatch Logs log group where chat activity will be logged.

DeliveryStreamName.Description: Name of the Amazon Kinesis Firehose delivery stream where chat activity will be logged.

BucketName.Description: Name of the Amazon S3 bucket where chat activity will be logged.

Key.Description: The key name of the tag. You can specify a value that is 1 to 128 Unicode characters in length and cannot be prefixed with aws:. You can use any of the following characters: the set of Unicode letters, digits, whitespace, _, ., /, =, +, and -.

Value.Description: The value for the tag. You can specify a value that is 0 to 256 Unicode characters in length and cannot be prefixed with aws:. You can use any of the following characters: the set of Unicode letters, digits, whitespace, _, ., /, =, +, and -.

Arn.Description: LoggingConfiguration ARN is automatically generated on creation and assigned as the unique identifier.

Id.Description: The system-generated ID of the logging configuration.

Name.Description: The name of the logging configuration. The value does not need to be unique.

State.Description: The state of the logging configuration. When the state is ACTIVE, the configuration is ready to log chat content.

Tags.Description: An array of key-value pairs to apply to this resource.

FallbackResult.Description: Specifies the fallback behavior if the handler does not return a valid response, encounters an error, or times out.

Uri.Description: Identifier of the message review handler.

Key.Description: The key name of the tag. You can specify a value that is 1 to 128 Unicode characters in length and cannot be prefixed with aws:. You can use any of the following characters: the set of Unicode letters, digits, whitespace, _, ., /, =, +, and -.

Value.Description: The value for the tag. You can specify a value that is 0 to 256 Unicode characters in length and cannot be prefixed with aws:. You can use any of the following characters: the set of Unicode letters, digits, whitespace, _, ., /, =, +, and -.

Arn.Description: Room ARN is automatically generated on creation and assigned as the unique identifier.

Id.Description: The system-generated ID of the room.

LoggingConfigurationIdentifiers.Description: Array of logging configuration identifiers attached to the room.

MaximumMessageLength.Description: The maximum number of characters in a single message.

MaximumMessageRatePerSecond.Description: The maximum number of messages per second that can be sent to the room.

Name.Description: The name of the room. The value does not need to be unique.

Tags.Description: An array of key-value pairs to apply to this resource.
